
[1]situated

   SIT'UATED, a. [See Siluate.]

   1. Seated, placed or standing with respect to any other object; as a
   city situated on a declivity, or in front of a lake; a town well
   situated for trade or manufactures; an observatory well situated for
   observation of the stars. New York is situated in the forty first
   degree of N. latitude.

   2. Placed or being in any state or condition with regard to men or
   things. Observe how the executor is situated with respect to the heirs.
